ManyÂ investorsÂ use a risk/reward ratio to compare theÂ expected returnsÂ of an investment with the amount of risk undertaken to capture these returns. This ratio is calculated mathematically by dividing the amount the individual stands to lose if the price of an asset moves in the unexpected direction (the risk) by the amount of profit theÂ traderÂ expects to have made when the position is closed (the reward)This ratio should be superior to 2, it means that you risk 1 to make 2 â€¼ï¸That's how you should trade on the market ğŸ‘Œ

https://www.tradingview.com/x/JeV0bsF0/#BTC UPDATE : As for wave analysis, on the H1 graph, we don't see the finished 5th wave and divergence, which could unequivocally tell about the end of a local fall.At the same time, the fall from $ 4130 to $ 3510 occurred without normal kickbacks, which is normal for stretching in waves, but indicates a future correction. After the end of the local fall in the wave (5 in blue), I expect growth in the form of a correction of this fall. Some traders expect a general increase after this fall to  4200$-4500$ Therefore, Im more inclined to think that this will be a fall correction, which will reach 0.38 ($ 3,750) / 0.50 ($ 3,820) - 0.62 ($ 3,900) Fibbo levels, after which we will continue to fall and refresh the lows. At the same time, this scenario will be locally incorrect if the price goes above $ 4000-4130.It's better to not enter on a short on this level the downward movement may not be large, in which case the risk will not correspond to the profit.
